external_knowledge:
- In project management, a project or model is considered to be "on target" if the actual runtime matches the estimated runtime;
- A project or model is said to have an "overrun" if the actual runtime exceeds the estimated runtime, indicating delays;
- Conversely, a project or model is said to have an "underrun" if the actual runtime is less than the estimated runtime, indicating efficiency or possibly scope reduction.

- `model_name` refers to the name of the model, similar to the title of a book;
- `version_number` refers to the specific version of the model, similar to the edition of a book;
- `status` refers to the current status of the project, such as whether it is active, completed, or on hold;
- `lead_researcher_name` refers to the full name of the lead researcher or project manager, similar to the author of a book.

sql:
SELECT AVG(m.actual_runtime) AS average_runtime
FROM models m
WHERE m.project_id = 0 AND m.status = 'production';

